":{"file":"swarm-do/roles/agent-spec-review/shared.md","line":54,"symbol":"Output format","snippet":"## Spec Review\\n### Verdict: APPROVED | SPEC_MISMATCH | SPEC_AMBIGUOUS\\n### Mismatches (if SPEC_MISMATCH)\\n1. <analysis requirement> vs <writer output at file:line> — what is off"},"recommendation":"agent-spec-review emits free-form markdown; the orchestrator cannot 'auto-discard rejections missing evidence' (plan:335-336) by schema validation without a structured artifact. Add a `spec-review-findings.v1.schema.json` with required `file`, `line_start`, `rule_id`, `evidence_snippet` fields, and route the role through a writer similar to extract-phase.sh (README.md:52) so rows land in findings.v2 with stable_finding_hash_v1. Regex-extracting file:line from markdown is fragile and will false-reject valid reviews.","confidence":0.9,"fingerprint":"spec-review-unstructured-output"},{"finding_id":"MCO-1.12d-004","severity":"high","category":"maintainability","title":"Regression-test generator is a full new stage and blows 1.12d scope","evidence":{"file":"plans/swarm-do-1.12-orchestration-friction-fixes.md","line":337,"symbol":"generate-regression-test","snippet":"on close-with-reason `bugfix`, a `generate-regression-test` stage runs (opt-in preset), emits a pytest case, verifies fail-before / pass-after, and adds it to the suite."},"recommendation":"Split this into 1.12e. The generator requires: (a) fail-before verification, which means checking out pre-fix commit inside a worktree (depends on 1.12c per-unit commit model), (b) LLM-driven test synthesis, (c) test-suite integration, (d) preset opt-in wiring. Its complexity rivals 1.12a (checkpoint+resume+watchdog). The scorecard 'regression tests added for 100% of bug-class closes' (plan:380) is also too aggressive as a promotion gate.","confidence":0.85,"fingerprint":"regression-gen-scope-creep"},{"finding_id":"MCO-1.12d-005","severity":"high","category":"maintainability","title":"knowledge.jsonl write path, extraction rules, and retry semantics are not specified","evidence":{"file":"plans/swarm-do-1.12-orchestration-friction-fixes.md","line":162,"symbol":"knowledge extraction","snippet":"run_id, phase_id, bug_class, file, gotcha, regression_test_path (if generated), source (review_comment | bug_fix | post_mortem)"},"recommendation":"Unlike findings.jsonl (README.md:50-64) which pins write path to bin/extract-phase.sh and specifies a stable hash algorithm, 1.12d does not name a writer binary, an extractor, how `bug_class`/`gotcha` are derived (LLM vs regex vs structured role output), at which granularity rows are appended (per-role, per-stage, per-phase, per-retry), or deduplication on writer handoffs (plan:190-194). Add a concrete writer contract with fail-open semantics matching README.md:150-166.","confidence":0.9,"fingerprint":"knowledge-writer-unspecified"},{"finding_id":"MCO-1.12d-006","severity":"medium","category":"maintainability","title":"Orchestrator-side independent validation duplicates agent-review and belongs in 1.12c","evidence":{"file":"swarm-do/roles/agent-review/shared.md","line":32,"symbol":"Sequencing & ownership","snippet":"Run the test suite yourself; inspect linter output. Do not trust the writer's pasted output — re-run."},"recommendation":"agent-review already re-runs tests independently; 1.12d:334-336 adds a second independent runner in the orchestrator with no precedence contract. Decide: either the orchestrator runs tests (and agent-review consumes its artifact) or agent-review runs tests (and feeds spec-review). This is an execution-flow concern and is coupled to 1.12c's per-unit commit/spec-review sequencing (plan:312-325). Move to 1.12c or merge the two sub-phases for the validation pathway.","confidence":0.8,"fingerprint":"orchestrator-validation-misplaced"},{"finding_id":"MCO-1.12d-007","severity":"medium","category":"maintainability","title":"Priming step has no enforcement hook and the target roles do not all exist","evidence":{"file":"plans/swarm-do-1.12-orchestration-friction-fixes.md","line":331,"symbol":"prime from knowledge.jsonl","snippet":"Agents (research, writer, spec-review) prime from `knowledge.jsonl` through a small JSONL filter matching their file scope before starting (bounded to top-N rows to avoid context bloat)."},"recommendation":"Two gaps: (1) `agent-research` does not ship in swarm-do/roles/ today (only agent-analysis, agent-codex-review, agent-review, agent-spec-review, agent-writer). Either rename to agent-analysis or declare role creation in 1.12d's DoD. (2) 'top-N' is unquantified and the priming script is not named — SKILL.md:79-86 routes role personas through bin/load-role.sh; extend that path (or add a wrapper) so priming is enforced at dispatch time, not trusted to the agent's prompt.","confidence":0.85,"fingerprint":"priming-unenforced-missing-role"},{"finding_id":"MCO-1.12d-008","severity":"medium","category":"performance","title":"Priming overhead is not accounted for against the 1.12a writer budget","evidence":{"file":"plans/swarm-do-1.12-orchestration-friction-fixes.md","line":291,"symbol":"writer budget","snippet":"Defaults `tool_calls=50`, `estimated_tokens=60_000`, tunable per preset."},"recommendation":"1.12a caps writers at ~60k estimated tokens and 1.12d adds a priming overlay with no ceiling. Specify a per-role priming token budget (e.g. `knowledge_prime_max_tokens=4000`) that debits the writer budget, plus a hard truncation policy if top-N rows exceed it. Without this, priming can cause the very context-exhaustion the section is meant to fix.","confidence":0.75,"fingerprint":"priming-budget-unaccounted"},{"finding_id":"MCO-1.12d-009","severity":"medium","category":"bug","title":"No adjudication layer on knowledge rows creates a false-positive feedback loop","evidence":{"file":"swarm-do/schemas/telemetry/README.md","line":92,"symbol":"adjudications.jsonl","snippet":"a human (or dedicated adjudicator role) reads findings without knowing the backend that produced them and records TP | FP | Ambiguous. Used to calibrate precision over time."},"recommendation":"Findings flow through blinded adjudication; knowledge rows would bypass that and be primed into every future matching-scope agent. Add a verdict field (`adjudicated_tp|fp|pending`) and only prime rows with `tp` or `pending>=N`. Without this, a single wrong 'gotcha' becomes a self-reinforcing systemic bias and the 1.12d scorecard 'cut review comments by ≥20%' (plan:379) could be met via suppression rather than correctness.","confidence":0.7,"fingerprint":"knowledge-no-adjudication"},{"finding_id":"MCO-1.12d-010","severity":"medium","category":"maintainability","title":"Schema-validation auto-discard path has no retry contract that interacts with 1.12c retry cap","evidence":{"file":"plans/swarm-do-1.12-orchestration-friction-fixes.md","line":335,"symbol":"auto-discard","snippet":"rejections missing evidence are auto-discarded by the orchestrator and retried once."},"recommendation":"1.12c already defines `max 2 retries (3 iterations)` on SPEC_MISMATCH (plan:321-322). 1.12d adds 'retried once' for missing-evidence auto-discard — does this count against the 1.12c cap, reset it, or run in parallel? State the interaction explicitly or the retry governor becomes unpredictable under combined failure modes.","confidence":0.8,"fingerprint":"retry-cap-interaction"}]}
